apl_event.title: Javier Jara Performs

apl_event.body: The caterpillars are coming! The caterpillars are coming! Come build a place for them to eat and eat and eat before finally settling into their chrysalises for a most amazing metamorphosis. The habitats we build will be perfect for getting real close and observing what happens along the way from very hungry caterpillars to glorious monarch butterflies.

apl_event.title: Let's Learn About Leaves!
apl_event.body: Come join us under the long limbs of the mighty live oak tree in front of the library building! We will begin with a mini-lesson on tree parts and a story. Afterwards, the children will have an opportunity to make and label a leaf rubbing.

apl_event.title: Butterfly Gardening for Monarchs

Join Howson Branch Library and The Natural Gardener to learn how to help our endangered butterflies by growing the blooms they love and the milkweed they need to survive. Each attendee will be given a packet of seeds from Native American Seed Co. to get them started on their own journey of cultivating sustenance and beauty for our amazing Monarchs!

apl_event.title: Monarch Butterflies Exhibit
apl_event.body: Come see how it all begins! We plan to have milkweed plants/cuttings with eggs on the leaves in a safe enclosure. Throughout the Roots & Wings Festival (10/22-11/5), we hope that caterpillars, then chrysalises will appear. When the adult Monarch butterflies mature, they will be set free just outside of the library!
